<h1>Casual Use cases</h1>

<p><b><u>Create a new commander 1.0</u></b></p>
<p>Create a new commander(casual version)</p>

<p>Player wants to create a new commander. The player names their commander the system will 
<p>check if the name is valid. The player sets statistics for their commander, strength, intelligence and
<p>luck. The system checks if the total of these attributes add up to 30 (30 max)</p>

<p><b><u>Use case 3.0: Create a new building</u></b></p>
<p>Create a new building(casual version)</p>

<p>The Player wants to create a new building, The Player will be presented with a list of buildings. 
<p>The Player selects a building and the system checks to see if the player has the resources to build
<p>the selected building. If the player has the resources available they will be able to drag and drop
<p>their selected building to a chosen cell. The system checks if the target cell is free. If the cell
<p>is free then the selected building is constructed on the chosen cell. At any time prior to completing
<p>the building the Player can withdraw their building choice and resources will be reimbursed. The Use 
<p>case ends when the building is complete.</p>

<p><b><u>Use case 5.0:Create a new unit</u></b></p>
<p>Create a new unit(casual version)</p>

<p>Player wants to delegate their army into units, The player will be shown a list of units. the player
<p>must selects a unit, The system will check if the player has the required building needed to house 
<p>the unit.The player will select how many soldiers they want to delegate to that unit the system 
<p>checks if the needed resources are there if they are the unit is created. The new unit will be 
<p>created  The system  will reduce the army quantity after the unit is created.</p>





</body>
</html>
